&lt;Starrex Mining Corp Ltd> said a sharprise in its share price is based on speculation for favorableresults from its current underground diamond drilling programat its 35 pct owned Star Lake gold mine in northernSaskatchewan.    Starrex Mining shares rose 40 cts to 4.75 dlrs in tradingon the Toronto Stock Exchange.    The company said drilling results from the program whichstarted in late February are encouraging, "but it is too soonfor conclusions." Starrex did not disclose check assay resultsfrom the exploration program. Reuter&#3;